  "prompt": "How much does a car salesman get per car?",
  "response": "The commission a car salesman earns per car can vary widely depending on several factors, including the dealership's commission structure, the sales price of the car, and whether the car is new or used. Typically, car salesmen may earn a commission ranging from a few hundred dollars to several thousand dollars per vehicle sold. \n\nHere are some common structures:\n\n1. **Flat Rate**: Some dealerships pay a flat commission for every vehicle sold, which can range from $100 to $1,000 or more, depending on the dealership's policies.\n\n2. **Percentage of Profit**: Many dealerships offer a commission based on a percentage of the profit made on the sale of the car. This could range from 20% to 30% of the dealership's gross profit on the sale.\n\n3. **Tiers**: Some salespeople may earn more per vehicle sold if they meet certain sales thresholds, creating a tiered commission structure.\n\n4. **Bonuses and Incentives**: There may be additional bonuses for reaching sales goals, selling particular vehicles, or working with finance and insurance products.\n\nOverall, it's common for a car salesman to earn anywhere from a couple hundred dollars to over a thousand dollars per sale, but this can vary significantly based on the dealership and market.",
